Shows errors, warnings, and other inspection highlights inline. Simply install the plugin and inspection descriptions will appear on the right side of the lines. Shown inspection severities are Errors, Warnings, Weak Warnings, Server Problems, Typos, and other inspections from plugins or future IntelliJ versions that have a high enough severity level. Each severity has a different color, with support for both light and dark themes.

Sensei is a highly customizable IDE plugin to scan and fix vulnerable code as you type - with hundreds of downloadable secure coding recipes (rules) as well as an in-built ability to craft your own. Supported languages: Java, XML Developed for developers by developers, it enables you to: Instantly transform bad code to good code with expert recipes written by Secure Code Warrior’s in-house secure coding developers and architects - with years of collective experience in cybersecurity Release code faster as you do not need to wait for scans to finish or issues to surface during code review or pull requests
